						               													<description>With 6 board combinations this game will never be the same, face the villains to become a true hero.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game consists of:&amp;#10;1. 06 modular maps representing a mythological site: a) Olympus of the Gods, b) Forests of Hera, c) Parthenon of Hera, d) Workshop of Hephaestus, e) Depths of Poseidon and f) Kingdom of Hades. Each map has a door and a space in which the deity is imprisoned.&amp;#10;2. Deck of cards with 20 mythological figures (Cerberus, Hydra of Lerna, Minotaur, etc) with combat power defined by numbers from 1 to 6 (result to win or be defeated) and attack effect.&amp;#10;3. 04 hero figures&amp;#10;4. 01 Dice D6&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each turn the player rolls the die and moves as many spaces as the die result across the grid towards the space in which the deity is imprisoned. Upon reaching the prison space, a card of a mythological figure is revealed where a battle takes place. In battle, you roll a die and compare it to the powers of the mythological figure. Being the winner the player receives a special effect from each deity (Athena, Hephaestus etc) and chooses a new map to be connected. Being defeated suffers the effect of the card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When all the deities are freed and all the modular maps are posted, a final battle takes place on the Olympus of the Gods.&amp;#10;The battle is against Cronos who is imprisoning Zeus. To beat him, roll a D6 die and have the result 6.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The player who beats Cronos is the winner of the game&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
